This paper presents a new data structure for combining multiple binary search trees, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.AL). The paper also discusses various performance bounds and competitive ratios, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and combinatorics (cs.DM). Additionally, the paper uses techniques such as amortization and potential functions, which are common in computational complexity (cs.CC).
